This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with medical image segmentation using convolutional neural networks. It also involves data augmentation, which is a common technique used in computer vision. 

The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it discusses the training of CNNs and the use of probabilistic augmentation. 

Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is another likely sub-category as the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques to improve medical image segmentation. 

Neural networks (cs.NE) is also a possible sub-category as the paper specifically deals with convolutional neural networks. 

Finally, multimedia (cs.MM) is a less likely sub-category, but it could be relevant as the paper deals with medical images and their segmentation.
